\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360  \b \i0 \ul0 [*17]\b0 \i0 \ul0   Section 3 criminalizes immigrants for failing to do the impossible. For "DREAMers" like \b \i0 \ul0 Erika Andiola\b0 \i0 \ul0  of Phoenix, Arizona, this will have particularly cruel consequences. Ms. Andiola was brought to the United States at the age of eleven. She excelled scholastically and enrolled at Arizona State University, where she became an honor student and graduated in 2009 with a B.A. in Psychology. She aspires to work as a school counselor. n48 Having been brought into the United States without inspection, Ms. Andiola has no way to register. Under Section 3, she will at once be subject to misdemeanor liability. n49 And unless she flees her home state, she will face felony liability for subsequent arrests. n50
