\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 Congress created the U-Visa to give legal status to victims of certain crimes and to encourage  \b \i0 \ul0 [*19]\b0 \i0 \ul0   them to aid in the investigation and prosecution of crimes. n54 \b \i0 \ul0 Jane Doe #3,\b0 \i0 \ul0  n55 an immigrant from \b \i0 \ul0 [**35]\b0 \i0 \ul0   Mexico who now resides in Tucson, entered into a relationship with a man who became abusive. After he slashed her tires, destroyed her clothes, and defaced the walls of her apartment, Ms. Doe became afraid for her safety and that of her children. She immediately applied for U-status as a victim of violent crime, but it took fifteen months before she received a registration document. n56
