\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 Asylum is a legal protection afforded to persons with a "well-founded fear of persecution"  \b \i0 \ul0 [**36]\b0 \i0 \ul0   based on race, religion, nationality, sexuality, or other characteristics. n57 \b \i0 \ul0 Jane Doe #1,\b0 \i0 \ul0  n58 a thirty-five-year-old woman of South Asian descent, resides in Phoenix. Because she practices Catholicism, she was severely persecuted in her home country, which is Muslim. She was kidnapped and sexually assaulted, but authorities refused to investigate her attack. She and her family were forced to flee to the United  \b \i0 \ul0 [*20]\b0 \i0 \ul0   States. During the pendency of Ms. Doe's asylum application, she lacked a registration document.
\par \pard 
