\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 Martha, n65 of central Alabama, is married to a U.S. citizen, with whom she has a U.S. citizen son. She is in the process of adjusting her status, in compliance with federal law. After Alabama's copycat law went into effect, she was stopped in a parking lot, allegedly for not having her lights on. When she failed to provide proof of citizenship to local police, Martha was arrested for violating the new law. She spent three days in criminal confinement until immigration officials arrived to verify her status.
